cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.PL

The paper deals with using machine learning models for binary analysis tasks related to security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of neural networks and learning representations, which suggests the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves solving algorithm classification and vulnerability discovery tasks, which suggests the category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
